<title>INDIA: India Sundram Fasteners 96/97 net higher.</title>
<headline>India Sundram Fasteners 96/97 net higher.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year to March 31, 1997.</p>
<p>	    (in million rupees unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net profit		320.5    vs     303.7</p>
<p>    Sales		   3,468.6    vs   3,030.9</p>
<p>    Div (in rupees)	   5.0    vs	 5.0</p>
<p>    Shr (in rupees)	  31.38   vs	29.73</p>
<p>    Other income	     13.2    vs	11.2</p>
<p>    Expenditure	   2,838.8    vs   2,473.9</p>
<p>    Interest		  213.3    vs     144.3</p>
<p>    Gross Profit	    429.7    vs     423.9</p>
<p>    Depreciation	     76.2    vs	55.2</p>
<p>    Tax			  33.0    vs	65.0</p>
<p>Note - Madras-based Sundram Fasteners Ltd is one of India's major auto components maker.</p>
<p>Interest charges rose 48 percent due to higher borrowing costs and modernisation and expansion schemes. It added fixed assets worth 420 million rupees in 1996/97, the company said.</p>
<p>Exports grew 18 percent to 455.4 million rupees from 385.4 million despite stiff competition, it said.</p>
<p>--Bombay newsroom +91-22-265-9000</p>
